"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-16-france-launches-probe-alleged-cyberbullying-olympic-gender-row-boxer-khelif\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - France has launched a cyberbullying probe following a complaint by Algerian Olympic boxing champion Imane Khelif, who was at the centre of a gender controversy at the Paris Olympic Games, prosecutors said recently.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.882085485574391, \"rank\": 0.1332497635178883, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 22, \"end\": 28, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.882085485574391, \"rank\": 0.1332497635178883, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 89, \"end\": 97, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.999638495776094, \"rank\": 0.00020221211968993337, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421623295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The controversy has rapidly become a hot-button issue outside the ring, with politicians and celebrities including Donald Trump and Elon Musk weighing in.\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9969729631213649, \"rank\": 0.003036227646785078, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 370, \"end\": 379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The investigation was opened Tuesday into \\\"cyberharassment\\\" following the high-profile gender row at the Games, the Paris public prosecutor's office toldAFP.\", \"from\": 394, \"to\": 551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 510, \"end\": 515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999150532, \"rank\": 8.495272025481137e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athlete's lawyer Nabil Boudi said last week that Khelif, 25, had filed a complaint for online harassment, calling it a \\\"fight for justice\\\".\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 696, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The investigation will determine who was behind this misogynist, racist and sexist campaign, but will also have to concern itself with those who fed the online lynching,\\\" he said at the time.\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Central Office for Combating Crimes against Humanity and Hate Crimes has been tasked with the investigation.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 1004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to US magazineVariety, billionaire entrepreneur Musk and Harry Potter author JK Rowling have been named in the complaint.\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1019, \"end\": 1021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9944568374319894, \"rank\": 0.0052869717065810885, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Potter\", \"score\": 0.9996450469966734, \"rank\": 0.00035507231722071606, \"text\": \"Harry Potter\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Potter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harry_Potter\"}, {\"begin\": 1093, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"JK Rowling\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Former US President Trump, who is the Republican party's nominee in the 2024 presidential race, would also be part of the investigation,Varietysaid, citing the lawyer.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1146, \"end\": 1158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.999999999712827, \"rank\": 2.8704871750962903e-10, \"text\": \"President Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 1177, \"end\": 1193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Party_of_Minnesota\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.03660029624096e-14, \"text\": \"Republican party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Party_of_Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Party_of_Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif won the women's 66kg final against China's Yang Liu in a unanimous points decision, having been the focus of intense scrutiny in the French capital during the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1483, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1350, \"end\": 1355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999109736047174, \"rank\": 6.658856044186769e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1358, \"end\": 1366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"score\": 0.9999966834678135, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yang Liu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\"}, {\"begin\": 1448, \"end\": 1454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8518631518844298, \"rank\": 0.16310072917271365, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Together with Taiwan's Lin Yu-ting, who won the 57kg women's final, Khelif was disqualified from last year's world championships after they failed gender eligibility testing.\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1499, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9996170950004953, \"rank\": 0.00024954049968980855, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 1508, \"end\": 1519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However they were cleared to compete in Paris, setting the stage for one of the biggest controversies of the Games.\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1701, \"end\": 1706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999150532, \"rank\": 8.495272025481137e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The row in Paris erupted after Khelif won her bout against Italy's Angela Carini in just 46 seconds with two strong punches to the Italian's nose.\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1789, \"end\": 1794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999150532, \"rank\": 8.495272025481137e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1837, \"end\": 1842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.99559257953163, \"rank\": 0.002208873754560241, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999962103662667, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}, {\"begin\": 1909, \"end\": 1916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.6550949839702714, \"rank\": 0.5145621079993095, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trump said he would \\\"keep men out of women's sports\\\" and his running mate JD Vance described the bout as a \\\"grown man pummelling a woman in a boxing match\\\".\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 2082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1926, \"end\": 1931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999996514362, \"rank\": 3.4862256385756755e-10, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JD.com\", \"score\": 0.9740955146603655, \"rank\": 0.02657588344754745, \"text\": \"JD\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JD.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JD.com\"}, {\"begin\": 2003, \"end\": 2008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\", \"score\": 0.999999999960437, \"rank\": 2.8257464766503665e-11, \"text\": \"Vance\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zebulon_Baird_Vance\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rowling also weighed in, saying onXthat the Paris Olympics would be \\\"forever tarnished by the brutal injustice done to Carini\\\".\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2203, \"end\": 2209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999807854669339, \"rank\": 1.9214902187218496e-05, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Boxing Association's Russian president and Kremlin-linked oligarch, Umar Kremlev, has targeted both athletes, claiming that Khelif and Lin had undergone \\\"genetic testing that shows that these are men\\\".\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2217, \"end\": 2249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3197346786484804e-21, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2252, \"end\": 2269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 0.9974907020916229, \"rank\": 0.002515610324195356, \"text\": \"Russian president\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}, {\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\", \"score\": 0.9999860054969473, \"rank\": 1.3483046274410506e-05, \"text\": \"Umar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IBA were responsible for the world championships in 2023 that Lin and Khelif were thrown out of, but the IOC cleared them to box in Paris.\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2438, \"end\": 2441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9995076544781364, \"rank\": 0.00032016766216768266, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 2543, \"end\": 2546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.6788701032659115e-22, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2570, \"end\": 2575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999150532, \"rank\": 8.495272025481137e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2591, \"entities\": []}]}"